sentence: Looking at units outstanding versus one week prior within the universe of ETFs covered at ETF Channel, the biggest outflow was seen in the Consumer Staples Select Sector SPDR Fund ( XLP ), where 12,550,000 units were destroyed, or a 6.5% decrease week over week.
Among the largest underlying components of XLP, in morning trading today Procter & Gamble ( PG ) is off about 0.3%, and Coca-Cola Company ( KO ) is lower by about 0.1%.
And on a percentage change basis, the ETF with the biggest outflow was the iShares U.S.
Fixed Income Balanced Risk ETF (INC), which lost 150,000 of its units, representing a 20.0% decline in outstanding units compared to the week prior.
